The paper discusses training techniques and objectives for deep learning models, which are commonly studied in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), and natural language processing (cs.CL). The focus on personalization and curriculum learning also suggests a potential fit with cs.HC (human-computer interaction) or cs.ED (education technology), but these are less likely given the emphasis on technical methods and metrics.
